    <operative>
        <clause>
            <title>[Chairperson</title>
            <para>[NAME] was appointed chairperson of the meeting [and chaired the meeting throughout].]</para>
            <para>
                <emphasis role="italic">Note. This wording may not be necessary if the chairman of the company is
                    present at the meeting and is also to chair it. However, it is often included in board minutes for
                    the sake of clarity. In addition, if the chairman of the company is interested in the business to be
                    conducted at the meeting, it may be appropriate for another member of the board to either chair the
                    entire meeting or the relevant part of the meeting in which the chairman is interested. In such
                    circumstances, the minutes should make it clear whether that person is to chair the entire meeting
                    or only a portion of it.
                </emphasis>
            </para>
        </clause>
        <clause>
            <title>Notice and quorum</title>
            <subclause1>
                <para>The chairperson reported that due notice of the committee meeting had been given and that a quorum
                    was present. Accordingly, the chairperson declared the meeting open.
                </para>
            </subclause1>
        </clause>
        <clause>
            <title>Declarations of interest</title>
            <subclause1>
                <para>Each director present [declared their interest in the business to be transacted at the meeting in
                    accordance with the requirements of section 317 of the Companies Act 1985 and the Company's articles
                    of association
                    <emphasis role="bold">OR</emphasis>
                    confirmed that they had no interest, direct or indirect in any way in the business to be discussed
                    at the meeting which they were required by the articles of association of the Company or by section
                    317 of the Companies Act 1985 or otherwise to disclose [other than those matters which had already
                    been disclosed]].
                </para>
            </subclause1>
            <para>
                <emphasis role="italic">An interest for the purposes of section 317 of the Companies Act 1985 is very
                    widely drawn and includes the interests of any family member and contracts by the company with any
                    other company of which the director is a director. Non-compliance is an offence which is liable to a
                    fine.
                </emphasis>
            </para>
            <subclause1 condition="optional">
                <para>It was noted that pursuant to article [NUMBER] of the Company's articles of association, a
                    director may vote and form part of the quorum in relation to any matter in which they are
                    interested.
                </para>
            </subclause1>
            <para>
                <emphasis role="italic">Examine the company's articles of association for provisions relating to
                    directors' interests which may prohibit them from voting. See, for example, Regulation 94 of Table A
                    (Companies (Tables A-F) Regulations 1985, SI 1985/805, as amended).
                </emphasis>
            </para>
        </clause>
        <clause>
            <title>Business of the meeting</title>
            <subclause1>
                <para>The chairperson reported that the committee had been constituted pursuant to a resolution of the
                    board of directors passed on [DATE] to deal with the remaining formalities for completion of the
                    Company's acquisition as a going concern of the business and assets of [FULL NAME OF COMPANY] (
                    <defterm>Target Business</defterm>) on the terms set out in an agreement (<defterm>
                        Agreement</defterm>) between the Company and [FULL NAME OF SELLER] (<defterm>Seller</defterm>).
                </para>
            </subclause1>
        </clause>
        <clause>
            <title>Documents produced to the meeting</title>
            <subclause1>
                <para>The following documents were produced to the meeting:</para>
                <subclause2 condition="optional">
                    <para>Minutes of an extraordinary general meeting of the Company at which the resolution(s)
                        [approving the Agreement] and [ADD ANY OTHER RESOLUTIONS] as set out in the circular to
                        shareholders dated [DATE] [was
                        <emphasis role="bold">OR</emphasis>
                        were] passed;
                    </para>
                </subclause2>
                <subclause2>
                    <para>[LIST DOCUMENTS PROVIDING EVIDENCE OF SATISFACTION OF THE CONDITIONS OF THE AGREEMENT;]</para>
                </subclause2>
                <subclause2>
                    <para>[LIST COUNTERPART TRANSFERS AND ASSIGNMENTS OF SPECIFIC ASSETS REQUIRED AT COMPLETION].</para>
                </subclause2>
            </subclause1>
        </clause>
        <clause>
            <title>Resolutions</title>
            <subclause1>
                <para>Having carefully considered each of the documents produced, the meeting confirmed that the
                    conditions [set out in Schedule [NUMBER]] of the Agreement were satisfied and resolved that the
                    Agreement could proceed to completion.
                </para>
            </subclause1>
            <subclause1>
                <para>The meeting resolved in consideration of the sale to the Company of the Target Business to deliver
                    to the [Seller
                    <emphasis role="bold">OR</emphasis>
                    Seller's solicitors] a banker's draft for &#xa3;[AMOUNT] in favour of the [Seller
                    <emphasis role="bold">OR</emphasis>
                    Seller's solicitors] for the amount specified in the Agreement.
                </para>
            </subclause1>
            <subclause1>
                <para>The meeting further resolved to authorise any director and in the case of any document requiring
                    execution as a deed any two directors or any one director and the Company secretary to execute and
                    deliver to the [Seller
                    <emphasis role="bold">OR</emphasis>
                    Seller's solicitors] at completion the following documents as required by the Agreement:
                </para>
                <para>[LIST DOCUMENTS]</para>
            </subclause1>
        </clause>
        <clause>
            <title>Filing</title>
            <subclause1>
                <para>The chairperson instructed the Company Secretary to make all necessary and appropriate entries in
